# Authentication API Testing
# Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Login with the user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get user profile (requires authentication)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Refresh token
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 5. Request password reset
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com"
}

### 6. Reset password
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "RESET_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### 7. Logout
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 8. Test protected earthquake route (create earthquake - requires authentication)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/earthquake
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "magnitude": 5.5,
  "location": "Test Location",
  "depth": 10.5,
  "date_time": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
}

### 9. Test admin-only route (delete earthquake - requires admin/moderator role)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/earthquake/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE